						<summary>

						<p>Slab (No. 2) built into the sluice in a field called ‘Kambaḷagadde’.</p>						

						<p>Kulaśēkara, 1355 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1[27]7, Manmatha, Dhanus 27, Thursday</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1355 A.D., December 24.</hi></p>						

						<p>It registers a gift of land probably by the king when he was holding assembly in his palace at <hi rend="bold">Bārakūru.</hi> It refers to the village Kuṁbaragōru. All other details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
